How good is the model on predicting our Y variable

In order to predict the class (Y = 1 or Y = 0) we need to apply some threshold, by default we can use 0.5.

Confusion Matrix â€“ in rows we have observed values of Y and in columns we have predictions

conftab1

       
        FALSE TRUE

  1. problem is our sample â€“ it is not balanced (not 50/50)
  2. if our sample is unbalanced then using threshold 0.5 is meaningless â€“ we should use value that is closer to share of Ys==1 in our data.
  3. there is a room for optimization â€“ select threshold to maximize selected measures
conftab1 <- table(df$status == 1, pred_m4 >= 0.50)
conftab2 <- table(df$status == 1, pred_m4 >= 0.35)
prop.table(conftab1, margin = 1)
